			<div class="content" id="post-content-1579315">
									

<p>Nicely realized setting. Interesting development of the anomoly, various creatures are OHGODOHGODLAND-HAGFISHKILLITKILLITAAAAAAAHH!!!</p>
<p>*ahem*</p>
<p>Clean, tightly written, good wordcraft (if I can use that term without sounding even more pretentious than usual). I don't usually have time to get to the &quot;The act of reading is now subconcious, you are experiencing the story in your head&quot; stage of immersion in pieces this short, but I did here.</p>
<p>The picture of the disembodied head had kind of a &quot;Mordo, Master of the Dark Forces/third-tier Vegas show&quot; feel to it, but the other images worked fine and Mordo didn't jar me enough to knock me out of the groove.</p>
<p>The off-list SCP (&quot;alien&quot;) was, as you observed, a risk, but it was handled deftly enough as an &quot;eyes-only&quot; extra that I felt it worked well.</p>
<p>Overall: A fine specimen of an SCP. Moar plz.</p>
<p>+1</p>

